    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you finish a long rest, roll a d20 and record the number rolled. You can replace any attack roll, saving throw, or ability check made by you or a creature that you can see with this foretelling roll. You must choose to do so before the roll, and you can replace a roll in this way only once per turn.</p>\n<p>Each foretelling roll can be used only once. When you finish a long rest, you lose any unused foretelling rolls.</p>\n<p>You can select this feat more than once, gaining one additional foretelling roll each time you do.</p>",
